1. Open Power BI
Launch Power BI Desktop

Open a blank report

2. Import Data
If you're using SQL Server:

Click on Get Data > SQL Server

Enter the server name and database name

Choose how you want to import (DirectQuery/Import)

If your data is in Excel:

Click Get Data > Excel

Select your Excel file and choose the table/sheet

3. Load the Data
Once you select the data, click Load

You will see tables added to the Fields pane on the right

4. Transform Data (Optional but Recommended)
Click Transform Data to open Power Query Editor

Check for:

Null values

Incorrect data types

Extra rows/columns

Formatting issues

If there are no changes to be made, click Close & Apply

If there are changes, modify them â†’ then click Close & Apply after editing.
